==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immunity
<hw>Im*mu"ni*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Immunities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>immunitas</ets>,
fr. <ets>immunis</ets> free from a public service; pref. <ets>im-</ets>
not + <ets>munis</ets> complaisant, obliging, cf. <ets>munus</ets>
service, duty: cf. F. <ets>immunit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Common</er>,
and cf. <er>Mean</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Freedom or
exemption from any charge, duty, obligation, office, tax, imposition,
penalty, or service; a particular privilege; <as>as, the
<ex>immunities</ex> of the free cities of Germany; the
<ex>immunities</ex> of the clergy.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Freedom; exemption; <as>as, <ex>immunity</ex> from
error</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The state of being insusceptible to disease, certain
poisons, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>immunization</ent>⟦br⟧
